CIA Country Analysis and Clustering¶

Source: All these data sets are made up of data from the US government. https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/docs/faqs.html

Gain insights into similarity between countries and regions of the world by experimenting with different cluster amounts.

In [ ]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

scaler = StandardScaler()

scaled_X = scaler.fit_transform(X)

Creating and Fitting Kmeans Model¶

In [ ]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
In [ ]:
SSD = list()

for k in range(2,30):
    
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=k, n_init = 10)
    
    model.fit(scaled_X)
    
    SSD.append(model.inertia_)
In [ ]:
plt.plot(range(2,30),SSD,'o--')
plt.xlabel("K Value")
plt.ylabel(" Sum of Squared Distances");
In [ ]:
plt.plot(range(2,30),SSD,'o--')
plt.xlabel("K Value")
plt.ylabel(" Sum of Squared Distances")
plt.xlim(1,7);
In [ ]:
pd.Series(SSD).diff().plot(kind='bar');
